Notes: The 'row_id' likely serves as a unique identifier for each measurement record, making 'hasIdentifier' the most semantically appropriate property.
The 'patient_id' directly corresponds to the patient associated with the measurement, mapped via 'hasPatient'.
Measurement code naturally aligns with the 'hasCode' property pointing to a Code entity, representing the measurement type or test code.
The measurement value is a quantitative measure, best represented as a Quantity node linked via 'hasQuantity'.
Unit of measurement is best mapped to a 'Unit' node linked via 'hasUnit' from Quantity.
Measurement date naturally maps to the 'hasDateTime' property with an XML dateTime datatype.
